(0,5,0) -- (10,5,0);\end{tikzpicture}]]>
</latex-image>
        </image>

      </statement>
      <answer>
        <p>
          Orient the solid so that the <m>x</m>-axis is parallel to long side of the base.
          All cross<ndash />sections are trapezoids
          (at the far left, the trapezoid is a square;
          at the far right,
          the trapezoid has a top length of 0, making it a triangle).
          The area of the trapezoid at <m>x</m> is <m>A(x) = 1/2(-1/2x+5+5)(5) = -5/4x+25</m>.
          The volume is <m>187.5</m> units<m>^3</m>.
        </p>
      </answer>
    </exercise>
